<style>
  @keyframes rotate {
    from {
      transform: rotate(0deg);
    }
    to {
      transform: rotate(10deg);
    }
  }

  .rotate-animation {
    animation: rotate 1s infinite alternate; /* Rotates back and forth */
  }
</style>
<div>
  <h1 class="text-center" style="color: darkgreen; font-size: 4rem">Eco Drop</h1>
</div>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12 text-center py-3 rotate-animation">
      <img src="/images/icons/battery.jpg" alt="battery" class="mx-auto d-block img-fluid" />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<br /><br />
<div class="container">
  <div class="col-lg-6 mx-auto">
    <p class="lead mb-4 text-center fade-in">Welcome to Eco Drop. Here you can give a second life to electronic devices by offering to other people. Also you can find a used device that can be useful for you instead of throwing it away or before recycling it.</p>
    <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-sm-flex justify-content-sm-center mb-5">
      <a href="/products/new" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4 me-sm-3 give-away-btn" style="background-color: #1761ab">Give Away</a>
      <a href="/products" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg px-4 find-device-btn" style="border-color: #1761ab; color: #1761ab">Find Device</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row g-4 py-5 row-cols-1 row-cols-lg-3">
    <div class="feature col text-center">
      <div class="feature-icon d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-success bg-gradient fs-2 mb-3">
        <i class="bi bi-people-fill"></i>
      </div>
      <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">Total E-Waste Generation</h3>
      <p class="fade-in">On a per capita basis, the average e-waste generated by a person in Europe was around 16.2 kg in 2019.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature col text-center">
      <div class="feature-icon d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-success bg-gradient fs-2 mb-3">
        <i class="bi bi-lightning-fill"></i>
      </div>
      <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">Importance of Responsible Recycling</h3>
      <p class="fade-in">Recycling electronics requires less energy than extracting and processing raw materials. This contributes to energy efficiency and helps lower the carbon footprint associated with resource extraction and manufacturing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature col text-center">
      <div class="feature-icon d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-success bg-gradient fs-2 mb-3">
        <i class="bi bi-graph-up-arrow"></i>
      </div>
      <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">Circular Economy Potential</h3>
      <p class="fade-in">Transitioning to a circular economy for electronics, which emphasizes reuse, repair, and recycling, could result in a net benefit of $700 billion annually by 2030.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<style>
  .fade-in {
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out;
  }

  .fade-in.visible {
    opacity: 1;
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
    var fadeElements = document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in');

    function isElementInViewport(el) {
      var rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
      return rect.top >= 0 && rect.left >= 0 && rect.bottom <= (window.innerHeight || document.documentElement.clientHeight) && rect.right <= (window.innerWidth || document.documentElement.clientWidth);
    }

    function handleScroll() {
      fadeElements.forEach(function (element) {
        if (isElementInViewport(element)) {
          element.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    }

    // Initial check on page load
    handleScroll();

    // Listen for scroll events
    window.addEventListener('scroll', handleScroll);
  });
</script>

<!-- Apply the "fade-in" class to the element you want to fade in -->
